HEADWORD: Pygopod
<hw>Py"go*pod</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pygh`</grk> rump + <ets>-pod</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the Pygopodes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of serpentiform
lizards of the family <fam>Pygopodid⟦ae⟧</fam>, which have rudimentary
hind legs near the anal cleft, but lack fore legs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pygopodes</ent>⟦br⟧
